# Command Center — environment configuration
#
# Copy this file to `.env` and fill in the values you want. `.env` is gitignored.
#
# The Claude Agent SDK picks credentials in this order:
#   1. ANTHROPIC_API_KEY (below)  — pay-as-you-go; the recommended path
#   2. CLAUDE_CODE_USE_BEDROCK / VERTEX / FOUNDRY — enterprise cloud transports
#   3. Your locally-logged-in Claude Code CLI (`~/.claude/`) — personal use only
#
# If you leave ANTHROPIC_API_KEY unset AND you have `claude` CLI logged in
# locally, the SDK will inherit that OAuth session. Useful for your own
# personal tinkering; NOT for any product you plan to share with others.
# See README.md → Authentication for the ToS caveat.

# Your Anthropic API key (starts with sk-ant-). Get one at:
# https://console.anthropic.com/settings/keys
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...

# Server host + port. Default 127.0.0.1:3333 keeps the server off the LAN.
# Change HOST to 0.0.0.0 at your own risk — anyone on your network gets
# unauthenticated agent access.
# HOST=127.0.0.1
# PORT=3333
